        <h3>Root Cause Analysis</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Inconsistent Implementation:</strong> Some AI Chat tables have Result classes (3 exist), but others only in SQL file (2 missing)</li>
            <li><strong>Incomplete Pattern Adherence:</strong> Documentation and AiMessage classes were created properly; CodeSearchIndex, WebSearchResults, AiModelConfig were not</li>
            <li><strong>Missing Documentation:</strong> No guide on how to create Result classes or use DBSchemaManager for schema creation</li>
            <li><strong>Partial SQL Usage:</strong> SQL file exists as fallback, but application doesn't auto-execute it on startup</li>
            <li><strong>Next Steps:</strong> Document the pattern, create 2 missing Result classes, then document for future consistency</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Startup Behavior (Current)</h3>
        <pre><code>[2025-12-25 05:50:51] ... _initialize_ai_chat_schema - Table 'documentation_metadata_index' not found in ENCY database. Will be created on first admin request.
[2025-12-25 05:50:51] ... _initialize_ai_chat_schema - Table 'code_search_index' not found in ENCY database. Will be created on first admin request.
[2025-12-25 05:50:51] ... _initialize_ai_chat_schema - Table 'web_search_results' not found in ENCY database. Will be created on first admin request.
[2025-12-25 05:50:51] ... _initialize_ai_chat_schema - Table 'ai_model_config' not found in ENCY database. Will be created on first admin request.
[2025-12-25 05:50:51] ... _initialize_ai_chat_schema - Table 'documentation_role_access' not found in ENCY database. Will be created on first admin request.
[2025-12-25 05:50:51] ... _initialize_ai_chat_schema - AI Chat schema check complete.</code></pre>
        <p><strong>Issue:</strong> Message says "will be created on first admin request" but no admin action actually creates them. Tables remain missing.</p>
